install_failed.description:
The add-on could not be installed automatically:

{error}

The add-on repository may already have been added for you, so you only need to install the **Home Assistant MCP Server** add-on from the Add-on Store. The integration's services will still be set up — select **Submit** to finish.

embedded_server_start_failed.description:
The Home Assistant MCP Server could not be started inside Home Assistant:

{detail}

The integration's file and YAML services are unaffected. Check the Home Assistant logs, then disable and re-enable the in-process server in the integration options to retry.

embedded_package_install_failed.description:
Installing the ha-mcp package for the in-process server failed:

{detail}

Check the Home Assistant logs and network connectivity, then retry from the integration options.
